OL,3,CThe King appoints Jersey's 91st Bailiff
OL,5,FHe read law at the University of
OL,6,FExeter, studied for the English Bar,
OL,7,Fand practised as an English barrister
OL,8,Ffor several years before returning to
OL,9,FJersey in 2001.
OL,11,FHe qualified as a Jersey Advocate in
OL,12,F2003 and was later appointed by Her
OL,13,FLate Majesty The Queen to the office
OL,14,Fof Attorney General and Queen's
OL,15,FCounsel in May 2015.
OL,17,FOn 6 January 2020, he was appointed as
OL,18,FDeputy Bailiff.
