OL,3,CThe King appoints Jersey's 91st Bailiff
OL,5,FThe Bailiff is a crown-appointed role,
OL,6,Fresponsible for the orderly conduct of
OL,7,FJersey's States of Assembly.
OL,9,FLike the UK's Speaker of the House,
OL,10,Fthe Bailiff presides over States
OL,11,Fproceedings, but cannot vote.
OL,13,FThe Bailiff's seat in the States
OL,14,FAssembly is 7 inches higher than the
OL,15,FLieutenant-Governor's place. This is
OL,16,Fto emphasise that the Bailiff has
OL,17,Fprecedence over all matters concerning
OL,18,FJersey's governance.
