OL,3,CThe King appoints Jersey's 91st Bailiff
OL,5,FThe Bailiff is also the President of
OL,6,Fthe Royal Court and is responsible for
OL,7,Fofficial communication with UK
OL,8,Fauthorities.
OL,10,FThe Bailiff can usually only hold
OL,11,Foffice until the retirement age of 70,
OL,12,Fwhich will be specified in the Letters
OL,13,FPatent appointing them to their role.
OL,15,FIn the case of Sir Timothy Le Cocq,
OL,16,Fhis status as Bailiff would have
OL,17,Fceased to be on Wednesday 9 December
OL,18,F2026.
